Trying to convert XML to JSON using jsonxsl+xsltproc is failing when the data has an identityref with the prefix defined on the tag of the text.

For example, using following YANG modules:
```yang
module test {
  namespace "http://example.com/test";
  prefix t;

  import "test2" {
    prefix "t2";
  }

  container x {
    leaf y {
      type identityref {
        base "t2:dummy";
      }
    }
  }
}
```
```yang
module test2 {
  namespace "http://example.com/test2";
  prefix t2;
  identity dummy;
  identity alpha {
    base "dummy";
  }
}
```

Along with following data:
```xml
<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<data xmlns="urn:ietf:params:xml:ns:netconf:base:1.0">
  <x xmlns="http://example.com/test">
    <y xmlns:t2="http://example.com/test2">t2:alpha</y>
  </x>
</data>
```

Attempting to convert XML to JSON gives:
```bash
$ pyang -f jsonxsl -o test.xsl test.yang test2.yang
$ xsltproc test.xsl data.xml
Undefined namespace prefix: t2
{
  "test:x": {
```

yang2dsdl says that the data is valid:
```bash
$ yang2dsdl -t data -j -b test -v data.xml test.yang test2.yang
== Generating RELAX NG schema './test-data.rng'
Done.

== Generating Schematron schema './test-data.sch'
Done.

== Generating DSRL schema './test-data.dsrl'
Done.

== Validating grammar and datatypes ...
data.xml validates.

== Adding default values... done.

== Validating semantic constraints ...
No errors found.
```

I think the error is related to the level used for namespaces in jsonxsl-templates.xsl (line 270):
```
266     <xsl:variable name="modname">
267       <xsl:call-template name="nsuri-to-module">
268   <xsl:with-param
269       name="uri"
270       select="../namespace::*[name()=normalize-space($prf)]"/>
271       </xsl:call-template>
272     </xsl:variable>
```

It looks like select is using the parent's namespace information, so the newly defined prefix is not found

